  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The hypothesis was to check whether baseline anti-E1E2 antibodies could predict virological
      outcome in Hepatitis C virus (HCV)-infected patients receiving direct-acting antiviral
      treatment
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Presence of anti-E1E2 antibodies was previously associated with spontaneous cure of hepatitis
      C virus (HCV). The hypothesis was to check whether baseline anti-E1E2 antibodies could
      predict virological outcome in HCV-infected patients receiving direct-acting antiviral
      treatment
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
